pr_body:
**Description**
There are no known bugs in the code. I have tried to make sure there are no memory leaks and the coding style is followed. The coding style to be followed can be found [here](https://www.kernel.org/doc/html/latest/process/coding-style.html). The code can be tested by using [these ](https://github.com/fossasia/libsigrok/pull/8#issuecomment-875989025) commands on sigrok-cli. The _code_ _structure_ is expected to change as we add new instruments.

**Known Weakness**

- Trigger is not tested properly

- Possible memory leaks (assigned memory not freed)


**Issue**
Resolves #5 


**Status**
Ready for review

pr_title: Adding support of PSLab devboard to lisigrok -- Oscilloscope
pr_body:
**Description**
[PSLab ](https://pslab.io/) is an open source project with an aim to make scientific instruments accessible for everyone. PSLab device supports numerous instruments like oscilloscope, multimeter, logic analyzer, Wave Generator, etc. 
We plan to add support of all instruments to libsigrok over the summer. 

**Scope of this PR**
As discussed on IRC, to make the reviewing process easier, this PR will deal with integration of the oscilloscope instrument alone.

**Status**
Ready for review
